<div type="definition">
<p>HIGH AND STEEP.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. Xiǎn 險 (ant. píng 平 "level") refers to inaccessible precipitous and dangerous high terrain.</p>
<p>2. Yán 巖 (or yán 岩 ) focusses on height and steepness in a rocky landscape.</p>
<p>3. Qiào 峭 means extremely steep, and it lays an emphasis on a steepness of a mountain.</p>
<p>4. Jùn 峻 emphasises the height of a mountain.</p>
<p>NB: A large number of poetic words should be added here.</p>
        </div>
